# NFTGallery

## Overview

NFTGallery is a web application that allows users to explore and view Non-Fungible Tokens (NFTs) from various blockchain platforms. This project aims to provide a visually appealing and user-friendly interface for discovering and interacting with digital art, collectibles, and other NFT-based assets.

## Features

- **Browse NFT Collections**: Explore curated collections of NFTs, categorized by artists, themes, and platforms.
- **View NFT Details**: Click on individual NFTs to view detailed metadata, including description, creator information, and blockchain transaction details.
- **Search and Filter**: Search for specific NFTs or filter by criteria such as price range, platform, and rarity.
- **User Profiles**: Allow users to create profiles, save favorite NFTs, and track their collection.
- **Integration with Blockchain**: Fetch and display real-time data using blockchain APIs to ensure transparency and authenticity of NFTs.
- **Responsive Design**: Ensure the gallery is accessible and user-friendly across devices and screen sizes.

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

Ensure you have the following installed:
- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/) (version 14 or later)
- [npm](https://www.npmjs.com/) (version 6 or later)

### Installation

1. Clone the repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/NFTGallery.git
   cd NFTGallery
